Ì6¶U<?php exit; ?>a:1:{s:7:"content";s:486:"<p>Acceptance and Commitment Therapy (ACT) is a mindfulness-based form of Cognitive Behavioural therapy. The overarching aim of ACT is to help you to achieve two main goals: (1) to effectively handle painful thoughts and feelings, and (2) to create a rich, full and meaningful life. The ACT approach suggests that our attempts to control, limit, or push away inner experiences cause emotional suffering, by way of constricting our lives and disconnecting us from what we value most.</p>";}